Package crm.oilwhere.model

package crm.oilwhere.model
Defines the core domain entities of the OilWhere CRM application.

This package includes Java classes that represent the business objects such as customers, users, and roles. These objects are mapped to database tables and serve as the foundation of the application's data model.

  • Class
    Description
    Customer
    Represents a customer entity with details about each customer.
    CustomerSegmentFilter
    Abstract class for filtering customers based on specific segments.
    CustomerSpending
    Represents a customer's total spending as stored in the "customer_spending_ranked" table.
    HighValueCustomerFilter
    Filters customers based on their monetary value, selecting the top 10% of customers.
    LowValueCustomerFilter
    Filters customers based on their monetary value, selecting the bottom 20% of customers.
    MediumValueCustomerFilter
    Filters customers based on their monetary value, selecting the middle 60% of customers.
    Newsletter
    Represents a newsletter entity with details about each newsletter design.
    Purchase
    Represents a purchase record entity that maps to the "purchase_history" table in the database.
    Role
    Enum representing the different roles a user can have within the system.
    User
    Represents a user entity with credentials and role information.
